{
  "stem": "17135.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he changed his name, interesting enough, to [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Diamant, ?] so that people don't get mixed up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- and they both were very active involve in the Jewish-- in the [GERMAN] community.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were two communities in Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The-- call it indigenous German Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had their own synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Jews that came from Poland, they called them [GERMAN], eastern Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we belonged, of course, since my parents came from Poland, we belonged to the [GERMAN] community.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there was a very active-- and my father was all the time in the committee, in the-- in the [INAUDIBLE], they called this.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he also-- I remember once in awhile, he gave courses and taught other people the Talmud Gemara.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And-- but I very much remember is, Shabbat was really Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Was a day of-- of pray, a day of resting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was almost a tradition in Germany, after the-- the-- the-- the davening, after the prayer, they went to the park.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Each city had a beautiful park.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And you could see only Jews in the park.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Beautiful park with flowers, with-- with-- with-- with a little artificial lake.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we went home for dinner.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and-- and after dinner, my father used to give us always a lecture about the midrash.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the most interesting thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the midrash is really-- that tells the story of the Bible, more more-- let's put it this way-- in detail than the-- than the-- the Torah that you read, you know?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was most interesting when he gave us-- midrash means, really, explanation.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The [HEBREW] in Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That means to more explain the text of the Torah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and that-- that was so interesting.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sometimes we said more, more, more.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
